📰 #HongKong police arrested the chief editor and four executives of the pro-democracy newspaper @appledaily_hk on Thursday.

The paper has long been a thorn in #Beijing’s side due to its scathing criticism of #China’s 🇨🇳 authoritarian leaders.

@carysgarland reports ⤵️ https://t.co/n7T0fztHoM

This is the "most severe blow to media freedom in Hong Kong. Having said that the Apple Daily team are absolutely extraordinary in their determination and courage." 

